title: Bug 6322: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes
description: Bug 6322: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes. JDK 1.4 includes obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) etc.
OB: When opening the 'All types' dialog in JDK 1.4, obfuscated classes like 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', and 'd' are shown.
EB: The 'All types' dialog in JDK 1.4 should not display obfuscated classes.
SR:
To reproduce: 
1. Open the 'All types' dialog in JDK 1.4.
2. Observe the presence of obfuscated classes like 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', and 'd'.
